public void setResponseHeaders(com.google.api.client.http.HttpHeaders responseHeaders)
Sets the HTTP headers returned with the server response, or null. This member should only be non-null if this object was the top level element of a response. For example, a request that returns a single Link would include the response headers, while a request which returns an array of Link, would have a non-null response header in the enclosing object only.
